,Recommended,220820,3876513,"Posted: 30 September, 2013",all,Aussiedroid,"I didn't have high expectations for Zombie Driver HD, but it's suprisingly good fun mowing down zombies in your car! My fav mode to play is Slaughter (survival) where the zombies keep coming which also has an online scoreboard to challenge your friends. Story mode is repetitive and gets pretty boring; there is a lot of content for the money though! Blood Racing is OK but most enjoyable once you get a good ride. Decent array of weaponry & cars to choose from which are all upgradable (off course :p).http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=188479432I created a section in the guide above which has a quick list of what you get in the DLCs. Also covers things like the vehicles, game modes etc which might be helpful if you still want to get a better feel for the game.Definitely good value, a few weak points short of a classic but overall a solid, fun game!Worth checking out if you like top-down racing games.If you enjoyed reading this review, please followTrue Blue Reviewsfor more recommendations!"
,Recommended,220820,32267669,Posted: 8 June,all,bad_rain,"I've played the original edition few years ago. I can only recall that it wasn't really a good game - mediocre at best.Now, seeing the HD remaster at low price (sale, around 1€) promising better campaign, new features... Well, why not?Zombie Driver is an arcade vehicular-combat game. There's a campaign, that will take you around 6 hours to complete. Also, racing mode, survival mode and lots of achievements. The problem is, it's all a bit underwhelming. Zombie Driver never becomes anything more than a brainless, ultra-violent, mildly engaging arcade game. It's entertaining in short bursts, but falls to make a lasting impression. I must admit, as a stress relief - it could work (If you're into turning hundreds of zombies into red paste :)).I failed to find major changes in comparison to the original release (Boss fights? Tedious.). Good thing is, the game runs pretty smooth on almost everything, managing a steady 60fps even on low-end laptops.Is it worth it? Well, if you can get it on sale, around 1-3€.Don't waste your money on the DLCs. Additional cars are OP, making the game a complete cakewalk."
