76561198122163777,Recommended,220820,33784983,Posted: 25 July,all,Opal Knight,"Zombie Driver HD is a bit of a guilty pleasure.  With beautifully rendered maps, destructable environments, and swathes upon swathes of zombies to mow down this game is a pleasure to play.  There is a nice roster of vehicles to unlock, all with different strengths and plenty of upgrades and paint jobs available for all of them.  There are also three different play modes: story campaign, rampage racing, and slaughter survival mode which makes for a nice variety depending on what sort of mood you are in.  And there are plenty of achievements to unlock for each mode.I, personally, had some difficulty getting used to the controls, but the game itself runs very smoothly (I have a low to mid range gaming PC).  All in all it's a pretty well polished game, with a lot of ambiance and detail and plenty of options for play."
