76561198038132122,Recommended,220820,32346710,Posted: 11 June,all,ForestWolf,"Rating: mediocre (5/10)IntroductionZombie Driver is a top-down racing & shooting game in a modern setting with zombie invasion. You mostly get missions to either rescue someone, destroy or deliver something, while shooting or ramming tons of zombies on the way.Gameplay & Story: 4/10The story is quite simple, as it is with most zombie influenced games. The devs tried to implement some story ""twists"" but they are too obvious, so that it is quite clear how the game gonna end right early in the beginning. The story is told by mission descriptions that you receive and some minor dialogs with survivors. The gameplay is quite simple - select a car fitting the missions, fulfill the objectives and try to get secondary objective for some extra cash. The more zombies you destroy on the way, the more bonus cash you will get. Besides the story mode the game offers some survival and tournaments against KI.Combat & Challenge : 5/10Playing this game casually I did not encounter any serious challange, neither in story mode nor in tournament or survival. It is quite easy to finish the game in short time aswell win every race in tournament mode and reach golden medals in survival. The combat in Zombie Driver is consisting of mostly holding two butons down - firing your weapon and driving forward, well, with steering left and right from time to time. The weapons have limited ammo but once you upgrade them, it becomes really easy to finish the objectives on almost any car.Graphic & Interface : 4/10The graphics are nothing special, but do fit the game style. There are not many details to look at, mostly you just watch a red/green mass of squashed zombies. The interface is simplistic aswell, just showing you the most needed information to fulfill your mission.Progress & Mini-Games : 5/10Progress is fairly quick and simple in this game. Since it does not take long to finish the game, you wont get bored to also enjoy some tournaments or try yourself in the survival. Tournament mode receives some extra points for having different race types (destruction, race, time survival, etc.). This delivers a nice change to the game.Audio & Immersion : 5/10The weapon sound and music fit the game, are nothing special though. It is nice that they voice the mission description and dialogs, give a bit better immersion in the game. The world does feel apocalyptic especialy in later stages of the game, but it clearly does not let you dive too deep in the city of Zombie Driver.Side-NotesThis game is single player only.This game contains steam achievements and trade cards.This game offers none to minimal replayability. Survival is the only mode that would attract playing it again.This game offers some minor rankings for tournament and survival modes where you can compare your times and scores to other players.This game is fairly short - it took me 10 hours playtime to finish the story, all tournaments and get golden medal on all survival maps.SummaryZombie Driver can be considered a casual top-down zombie shooter, even if you race in a car instead of running. You will get fairly quick through the story and other modes, so even though the game is nothing special, you most like wont get bored in the short time invested.I hope this review helps you making the decision if its worth buying this game. Rate and leave a comment if you enjoyed reading it.~ForestWolf"
