,Recommended,220820,31930605,Posted: 24 May,all,『 科学のTetøra 』Shikaco,"TL;DR DOWN BELOWI find this game fun. And that is what's important; it is fun. Mowing down countless zombies for minutes on end is a great way to pass the time, especially with the game's straightforward run over and shoot mechanics. While other games such as Civ V or Stardew may eat your time away just as much (or perhaps more), those games need the player to think rather heavily, To some of us, having to use our heads can be a deterent into enjoying something. This is where Zombie Driver shines, it is a game of pure, mind numbing fun.That being said, its base price tag of $8-10~ isn't really justified, considering that I can spend  just as much for other titles that have more interesting gameplay mechanics, better writing, and better visuals while being capable of maintaining the same amount of enjoyment I can get from Zombie Driver. The game's current price is a bit too much for me, it feels like a $5 game even with the ""Complete Edition"" (which only adds in two maps for its ""Slaughter"" mode, a racing game mode, and some really lackluster car customization additions).Zombie Driver's most glaring issues are its lack of a free roam mode, shallow car customization (both gameplay upgrades and aesthetic options), and while it isnt really the focus of the game, -its writing. I really wish this game had free roam. Its Slaughter mode is kind of there but it's not enough as it limits you with getting a high score until your car is destroyed. This affects its replayability but not so much that I would turn my head away from this game. As the game progresses, the zombies get more and more harder to kill and thus an upgrade system was added but all the upgrades and car options seem so pointless and feels like padding when I ended up only using the Auroch truck with full upgrades due to its high health bar and stable handling. With the latter being almost crucial with all the cramped corners in the sub-urban areas. I tried my best in paying attention to the storyline but it was so generic and badly written that I ended up skipping dialogue to just go on ahead and play.I recommend this game. past that whole paragraph I just wrote, I still think the game is nice. But only if it's on sale. (I got its complete edition for more or less a dollar).TL;DR :Zombie Driver is fun at its purest form. it just has a price tag that you'd be better off spending on something more justified for $10. That, and its lacking car customization, story, and no free-roam. But don't let that stop you from getting it with even the smallest of price reductions."
