,Not Recommended,220820,31342024,Posted: 24 April,all,Nomine,"Checked out my wishlist after getting some wallet money from various trading cards and found this. Looked like a fun game of destruction and mayhem, but in reality it's not that fun after a while.There are only 4 guns that you upgrade with cash earned from kills/missions, but you can only use one at a time and have to pick another powerup to use the others. There is a combo counter on killing enemies, but said guns don't seem to contribute to it (unless the combo is already going?). The gameplay consists mainly of carefully drifting around the map, mowing down zombies with clunky controls and a locked player camera. You barely use your guns for any other purpose than shooting at a crowd of story objective targets or shooting at bigger enemies when they start appearing between big zombie hordes. It would be nice to be able to destroy the sturdier walls, too.There is a lack of control for aiming your weapons and handling the car (blood race mode especially), so I don't recommend the game."
