,Recommended,220820,2053424,"Posted: 16 September, 2013",all,Two Clicks,"A real joy to play.  Those of you who have played GTA2 & Nation Red can imagine that the gameplay is a mix between those two games.  Not quite a brainless top/down shooter, this game needs you to use just enough brainpower to keep things interesting.Though you're replaying mostly on the same map, different areas open up keeping navigating through the city beyond a preamble.  Unlike in RL you cant rely on your sat-nav to make your way to various missions points.  The campaign varies with enough objectives to avoid being boring and onces that finished you can replay it or play; Race & Suvivor mode for a variety of challenges.The real neat thing is that you can choose one of many cars you have to unlock by completing the missions.  Each of which can have further upgrades and better equipment and weapons puchased too by collecting money drops or killing zombies.All-inall this is a real cheap game that punches well above its level and never ceases to be enjoyable.  A nice gem of a game."
