76561198026336659,Recommended,220820,28733528,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,Calebbyars,"I mostly play games for story and unique gameplay elements, so take my review as a narrow minded and focused thing as I only played the story campaign, and I DID ENJOY IT, IF YOU CAN BUY IT CHEAP OR ON SALE, DO IT! Don't yell at me for what follows hahaPros:-Driving controls pretty tight-drifting is fun but I never really used it-graphics are super pretty for a game world you just speed through-visceral, gross, bloody, zombie fun completely as advertised-tank, truck, and one firefighter mission are cool and should have been more numerousCons:-you'll probably never upgrade more than 1 vehicle to max because they just get better as you find more so the bus and supercar are the only things you need in the end-VERY samey and repetitive missions that involve going to a circle and shooting the 2-3 zombie spawners nearby then mindlessly gunning down the remaining zombies.-you always have acess to all unlocked weapons, so there is no sense speciallizing in one set of upgrades-WAY TOO MANY BOMB ZOMBIES TOWARDS THE END, felt like I had to follow the speed limits not to hit them and lose the whole mission from doing the one thing the game is designed for...PLOWING DOWN ZOMBIES WITH MY MURDERCAR!-Weapons only face forwards so bossfights mostly just involve standing there firing, then driving to the health pickup a thousand times.-At the end of a mission, regardless of difficulty, distance, or health remaining you have to drive back to base which is pointless if you aren't rescuing anyone because the next mission just sends you out again immediately.-MY BIGGEST PROBLEM: as long as zombies wander into the mission zones, they aren't complete, so you may have to spend minutes just waiting for zombies to stop wandering from the world into the mission area so you can continue, and there's always the chance you'll pull more if you drive out to kill them. I know the point of the game is to kill zombies, but if you play this for more than an hour straight it becomes more about the missions than the zombies, which feel like more of an inconvenience than a fun challenge.Summary:I had fun with the first 2 hours of my 7 hour playtime, but once you've done one of the two truck and two tank missions, you've seen everything the game has to offer minus a few hours of driving and cleaning zombie guts off the windshield...P.S. Way to make a plot pun out of your game name, if it wasn't for the fact that it started at the middle of the game and every rescue mentioned it, it would almost be a funny surprise at the end."
