,Recommended,220820,31905719,Posted: 22 May,all,Indurok,"Video version of this review:http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=930965579This game begins with an explosion of some chemical plant that turns people into zombies, and your character escapes in a taxi car. Does this guy work for the taxi company, or did he just steal it because it was the closest means of escape? I don’t know, but who cares? The point is, you are hired by the military to mow down zombies, rescue survivors, and upgrade your vehicle.With each zombie you kill, you earn money, which you use to purchase upgrades for your car. You can also get money by picking it up off the ground, or completing the secondary missions. You get multiple different upgrades for your vehicles, like weapons and abilities. Each car has different stats, such as how far upgraded the abilities are when you get the vehicle, as well as how many passengers that particular vehicle can carry. So you better choose wisely for your next mission.There are some vehicles you can drive but you cannot unlock, because you can only drive them on certain missions, like a truck, a tank, a bulldozer, and a firetruck. Unfortunately, these vehicles cannot be upgraded with weapons and abilities, so you’re gonna need to keep an eye out for health. I really love the tank, because you got the big gun, which is great for destroying clusters of zombies.And of course, like any other zombie video game, there are different kinds of zombies. The regular walkers, who apparently can throw stuff at you. Rude! And there are some bigger guys who are stronger, and more difficult to run over. It’s best to use your boost on these guys because they actually slow your car down. And what would a zombie game be without an exploding zombie? I don’t think I need to explain these ones. They just explode when you get near them. And the dogs go without saying. They just run at you and attack, and are faster than the human zombies.You also have to fight bosses as well; giant mutant creatures that throw goo at you, spray toxic... blood or whatever at you, and are extremely ugly.The game is a ton of fun... when you’re not constantly driving straight into an exploding zombie. It’s probably just because I suck at video game driving, but after a while, it just gets kinda ridiculous. And there seem to be times when health can be scarce, most likely because I’ve just been looking in the wrong places. But honestly, I’ve driven for several blocks through alleyways, and not seen a speck of health when I desperately need it. And it’s kind of annoying when you hit something and your vehicle ends up spinning out of control. It tends to turn me the opposite direction of where I want to go, or flip me on my side, and I have to respawn in a place where I’m surrounded by zombies who kill me instantly because of my LOW HEALTH!I was a little disappointed with the ending. I don’t know if this counts as a spoiler, because characters have been talking about it throughout the entire game. Plus, it’s kinda something pretty much anyone would half expect from a zombie game. They keep saying the military is up to something, but I don’t remember seeing anything indicating what or why.But all of my problems aside, this is actually a good game, and I totally recommend you check it out."
