76561198043671770,Recommended,220820,31341364,Posted: 24 April,all,Mutini,"Havent played for very long yet but Ill go out on a limb and say that this game is well worth the 99 cents being asked for it right now.  Its basically a top down shooter, zombie squisher with objectives and a silly but fun story line to keep things progressing in a certain direction.  Neither story nor game play are going to win any big awards but the game is a fun/mindless way to blow some time when your bored.  The story mode consists of various compartmentalized events that contain objectives, like rescue and recon missions.  You do these missions one at a time, meaning that you get your orders, go to the car customization screen to choose and upgrade your vehicle and then do the mission.  When the mission is over, you repeat the sequence for the next mission.  As you might expect, the missions become more difficult as the game progresses.  There are two other modes of game play for this game but I havent played them yet so I cant comment on them.  Ive only played a bit of the story mode.  I would imagine that one of the other modes of play involve a ""hold out"" mode where you survive as long as you can and kill as many zombies as possible during that time period.  I forget what the other mode is.  So yeah, for what this game is and what it costs, you cant go wrong by adding it to your library.  Just dont expect this ""game"" to reflect real life in anyway like one of the reviewers I read who thinks that its unrealistic that the Army doesnt just take care of all the problems.  Guess he thinks it breaks the immersion?  immersion in this game? Really??   Besides, if the army took care of all the problems in the game then what exactly would the player have to do?"
