,Recommended,220820,31404621,Posted: 27 April,all,BurnoutGT45,"Zombie Driver HDWhat a name. A name like that makes a game sound so generic and dull, yet this one is tons of fun. It's basically 3 games in one, in the sense that some mechanics are shared between them but the rules are quite different, like Kirby Air Ride. On that note, let's start with...Story ModeThe story of Zombie Driver HD involves a chemical outbreakbecause some pharmaceutical company wanted to find a cure for cancerthat turns most of the population into zombies (obviously) except for one man in a taxi, who ends up working with the military to help save as many people as possible. Ok, now that the synopsis is out of the way, this mode is the weakest one in my opinion. The mission variety is pretty good, with a couple boss fights and some special vehicle missions (the tank ones are a blast) breaking up the monotony of having to drive to ANOTHER location across the city to rescue people. It's not like the rescue missions are bad, it's just that most of the story mode is rescuing people and it can get repetitive after a while. The story, though, is so cliché it drags things down.The moment the cat scratches you in Mission 19, I knew the story was going to end with a zombie reveal jump scare. By the way, the military was using you the whole time so they didn't have to do any dirty work themselves. Nuke the city, leave no trace, did no work, pretend nothing happened, how original. /sTLDR:Mostly fun missions and bosses, lame and predictable story. I score it 3 bad voice acting jobs out of 5.Blood Race ModeThis mode is practically Twisted Metal meets Burnout, but top down. For what was originally a free update for the original game, Blood Race is pretty great. It's not just races either; Elimination events are basically deathmatch races (as crazy as that sounds, it actually works) and Endurance events are where the zombies really get involved, where you have to try and keep killing them while also destroying roadside obstacles to extend your time limit. If it wasn't for the ridiculous rubber-banding by the AI in the races (they literally have super tire grip and do not have to slow down in corners at all, and then they slow down to a snail's pace when they pass you) this mode would have been perfect but as is, it's just very solid. 4/5 stars easy.Slaughter ModeEasily the best part of Zombie Driver HD, the Slaughter Mode is an endless horde mode where you drive a car around a moderately sized arena of your choice (there's quite a few to pick from) and try to stay alive as long as possible. After a set amount of kills, an upgrade drops which may give you access to sporadic weapon drops or turbo, and there are health pickups to help make the surviving a little easier. There isn't much else to say here because not much else needs to be said; Great stress relief and highly replayable for score seekers, 5 stars.Recommendation:(3 + 4 + 5) / 3 = ...ah, forget it, no need for math here. Weak story and absurd race rubber-banding aside, Zombie Driver HD is a fantastic top-down action racing game. If I had to score it: ★★★★½ (the extra half star because of how much fun the whole thing is. No, really.)"
