,Recommended,220820,35211696,Posted: 25 September,all,JohnBart,"Years ago, I used to play the original Zombie Driver, a funny if somewhat lackluster action-driving game. The HD ""remaster"" is a huge improvement in every aspect compared to the original.New missions and mission types, special assignments with mission-specific vehicles (such as tanks, bulldozers or military trucks), revamped graphics and destruction physics, and a much-needed gameplay rebalance (e.g. a better flow of cash after gore-mayhem-and-destruction, and more frequent powerup placement on the game map) make the HD version the definite experience of the game. The besieged city is more atmospheric and alive (?) thanks to the extra cutscenes and the zombie-killing military allies, the new spawnnests and minibosses spice up the enemy variety well enough, while the new weather conditions (fog, bloom, rain, and night missions) also spice up the flow of simple, yet fun missions.Besides the main story mode, there is also a Carmageddon-esque Blood Race mode and the obligatory Survival gameplay as well - none of which were present in the original game, and which also add some longevity to the overall experience.In short, the game is a perfect no-brainer (pun intended) destruction-based top-down shooter, as simple as you might expect by its title. Missions may be repetitive in the long run, voice acting is a bit annoying, and the unskippable cutscenes do more harm than good for the gameplay, but these do not really detract from the overall experience. I really recommend it if you are looking for a simple, yet fun destruction-based vehicle shooter."
